      "content": "While it is true that antibiotics can affect gut bacteria, the risk of incomplete pathogen eradication is generally considered a greater threat. If you stopped now, the infection could flare up later, potentially requiring stronger or different treatments. Please consult with your prescribing doctor to discuss if an adjusted course is appropriate, but generally, finishing what was prescribed is the safest course of action.",
